CCR LaTeX Template License
==========================

This repository is dual-licensed. Two classes of content are covered by
two different licenses, and which license applies depends on which file
you are using:

  Code
    The LaTeX class file ccr.cls (and any accompanying source code such
    as build scripts or filter files) is licensed under the MIT License.
    See below.

  Example content
    The files main.tex, body.tex, bibliography.bib, and aup_logo.pdf,
    along with any rendered PDF produced from them, are licensed under
    the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International license
    (CC BY 4.0). See below.

Articles typeset with this template and published in CCR are released
under CC BY 4.0 as part of the journal's open-access policy,
independent of the template's own license terms.

Copyright (c) 2023-2026 Wouter van Atteveldt, Damian Trilling,
Chung-hong Chan, Johannes B. Gruber, Rupert Kiddle, and contributors
to the ccr-journal organization on GitHub.


